  [ 0  cos(φ) -sin(φ) ]
  [ 0  sin(φ)  cos(φ) ]
  ```
  So, `rotR (x₀)` applied to the vector `(cos(x₂)x₁ - sin(x₂)x₂, sin(x₂)x₁ + cos(x₂)x₂, x₃)` would be:
