- `rotM (x.1) (x.2)` is a rotation matrix that rotates the vector `(x.1, x.2, 0)` around the z-axis by an angle `θ = arctan(x.2 / x.1)` (if `x.1 ≠ 0`). If `x.1 = 0`, it's a degenerate case.
